# Self-Test

Use this after coordinating a real Burpvalve turn.

- [ ] I preserved one atomic payload per gated commit.
- [ ] I verified the staged hash before requesting verifier verdicts.
- [ ] I used real verifier evidence and preserved disagreements.
- [ ] I treated terminal wakes as attention routing, not evidence.
- [ ] I released file and gate reservations after commit or abort.
- [ ] I recorded commit, attestation, verifier, and work-unit refs in the handoff.
- [ ] I stopped instead of widening scope when the payload boundary was unclear.

Stop using the skill when there is no active work unit, no queued owner, and no
coordination decision to make.
